column5: Great vid!  New Zealand is just below Alaska on "the list" for me - I have some friends down there too
That was cool. With all the dragon flies being taken, I thought it was an a dead dragon fly being taken until the line went tight.  Ven
I actually have a couple dragon fly lures, they are great. Made by river2sea.
In situations like that I always struck too soon, at the bulge, and pulled it away before the fish had it. Watching the leader line junction really helps. Great video
I try to see the take, say the word "trout" and then strike, easier said than done sometimes though
Actually they are not dragon flies though in the same family. They are damsel flies.
Actually they are not dragon flies though in the same family. They are damsel flies.  There's a fine line between a damsel and a dragon
